verbose_text: Although there were strong relationships between SREBP1c mRNA expression and both the total n-3 and total n-6 concentrations, we found that the strongest predictor of SREBP1c mRNA in omental adipose tissue was the total content of n-6 PUFA in the phospholipids of the red blood cells, and the inverse relationship between n-3 content and SREBP1c expression did not persist when adjustment was made for total n-6 levels.
